tivity to the faint $\\gamma$-ray emission from the\nvery extended Vela X region, a multivariate analysis method combining three\ncomplementary reconstruction techniques of Cherenkov-shower images is applied\nfor the selection of $\\gamma$-ray events. The analysis is performed with the\nOn/Off background method, which estimates the background from separate\nobservations pointing away from Vela X; towards regions free of $\\gamma$-ray\nsources but with comparable observation conditions. The $\\gamma$-ray surface\nbrightness over the large Vela X region reveals that the detection of\nnon-thermal VHE $\\gamma$-ray emission from the PWN HESS $\\mathrm{J0835\\mhyphen\n455}$ is statistically significant over a region of radius 1.2$^{\\circ}$ around\nthe position $\\alpha$ = 08$^{\\mathrm{h}}$ 35$^{\\mathrm{m}}$ 00$^{\\mathrm{s}}$,\n$\\delta$ = -45$^{\\circ}$ 36$^{\\mathrm{\\prime}}$\n00$^{\\mathrm{\\prime}\\mathrm{\\prime}}$ (J2000).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Oct 2012 09:54:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-14"}
