ransition from a type IIn to a\nstandard type II SN. Modelling the observations of SNe 2009dd, 2010aj and\n1995ad with radiation hydrodynamics codes, we infer kinetic plus thermal\nenergies of about 0.2-0.5 foe, initial radii of 2-5$\\times10^{13}$ cm and\nejected masses of $\\sim$5.0-9.5 Msun. These values suggest moderate-mass,\nsuper-asymptotic giant branch (SAGB) or red super-giants (RSG) stars as SN\nprecursors, in analogy with other luminous type IIP SNe 2007od and 2009bw.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Oct 2012 12:28:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 May 2013 11:36:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
